Description: Seven body sherds, Nubian handmade, from different vessels, Kerma Ancien?. Five of them have labels: A: AWS 208, E. Bank, near house, red on both sides, very well polished, painted decoration (a circle?) on the outside. B: AWS 199, very eroded, dotted lines. C: AWS 208, dotted lines. D: AWS 301, incised diagonal lines. E: AW 38/9, X, ... Am 117, dotted lines.
Acquisition notes: Formerly housed by the Birmingham Museum and Art Gallery and the EES London.
